OL,4,Cfollowing angling trip in Thames Valley
OL,6,FThames Water has been taking samples
OL,7,Ffrom the river in Henley to check for
OL,8,Fpollution.
OL,10,FThe samples were taken from two
OL,11,Flocations - Hambleden and Marsh Locks
OL,12,F- over the past two months.
OL,14,FThe company said the results show that
OL,15,Fon the vast majority of occasions, the
OL,16,Fwater quality reaches Environment
OL,17,FAgency bathing standards.
OL,19,FThere were two instances of pollution
OL,20,Fafter rainfall but Thames Water said
OL,21,Fit wasn't down to them.
